        <para id="id295520">Having acquired all the information we require we can now calculate the cost of the <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>h</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub></m:math>:</para>
        <equation id="uid23">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mtable displaystyle="true">
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mi> Cost </m:mi>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                        <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:munderover>
                      <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>ν</m:mi>
                    </m:munderover>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>ω</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>λ</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">csc</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">csc</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">csc</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:msup>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                            <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                            <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                        </m:msup>
                        <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                        <m:msup>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                        </m:msup>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msqrt>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">csc</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:msqrt>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:msup>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                            <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                            <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                        </m:msup>
                        <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                        <m:msup>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                            <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                            <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                        </m:msup>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msqrt>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cos</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
            </m:mtable>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id295976">In order to check that the perturbation lowers the cost for some sufficiently small <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> we
differentiate this expression and evaluate the derivate at <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math>
Even further simplification reduces the formula to the following somewhat complicated expression:</para>
        <equation id="id296011">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mtable displaystyle="true">
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mfrac>
                    <m:mi> Cost </m:mi>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                          <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                          <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mo>|</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>[</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">csc</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cos</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                    <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cos</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>]</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mfenced separators="" open="|" close="|">
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>f</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mfenced>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>[</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">csc</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cos</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msup>
                    <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                      <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                      <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">sin</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>φ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo form="prefix">cot</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>θ</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo>]</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
            </m:mtable>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id296343">With the help of the above analsysis, we have shown that</para><equation id="id296356">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mfrac>
              <m:mi> Cost </m:mi>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:msub>
                  <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                    <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:msub>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mo>|</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>h</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo>&lt;</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id296413">independent of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>l</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>φ</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> This proves the claim that two dimensional trusses
cannot have corners.</para>
      </section>
      <section id="uid24">
        <title>Other Deformations</title>
        <para id="id296456">Other deformations of trusses worth considering are
perturbations of other junctions. Consider the case when
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mo>⋯</m:mo><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math> are beams meeting at a point <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>p</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> Suppose we shorten
each beam by introducing a polyhedron about <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:math> whose <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:math> vertices
meet the beams <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mo>⋯</m:mo><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math> and each edge represents the location of a new beam.
From Lemma 4 above we see that the cost does not change with
the perturbation if the junction consists of only cables of only bars. This study
would help rule out certain cases when both cables and bars meet at a junction.</para>
        <para id="id296552">A second deformation consists of making piecewise affine deformations
within a triangle as follows; divide the triangle into three sub-triangles
with common vertex in the center. Choose a base and let <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> be the affine transformation of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>
which maps points <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> to points <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> whose distance to the line passing through the base is
scaled by <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>ρ</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> The affine transformations in the remaining triangles is uniquely determined by continuity.
Thus, <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>η</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> be the unique piecewise affine transformation of <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:math>
with <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>η</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> for <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> not in the triangle and <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>η</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> for <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> in the first sub-triangle.
Applying <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>η</m:mi><m:mi>ρ</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> to a truss and then adding the necessary beams to ensure that is equilibrated
then yields the perturbation.</para>
      </section>
    </section>
